The{Lothian Players}is an amateur theatre company in Haddington which includes the{Theatre of Youth}- the junior section. They perform three productions a year. One production takes place during the{Haddington {Festival}and then continues its run in the{Edinburgh Fringe Festival.}There is also a pantomine in the winter season.
There is no longer a cinema in Haddington. The cinema building is now a{bingo hall.}
Both dancing and instrumental instruction are available.
{Discos}and{dances}are held in local hotels and Corn Exchange. The school hosts occasional{concerts.}
